HEADWORD: Inoxidizable
<hw>In*ox"idi`za*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Incapable of being oxidized; <as>as, gold and platinum are
<ex>inoxidizable</ex> in the air</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

